VII. But those who had gone thither before the war, may, it would seem, by the law of nations, be held for enemiesrafter a mode- rate time within which they could depart. And thus the Corcymans, when about to besiege Epidamnus, first gave allowance to strangers to depart, and announced that if they did not, they would hold them for enemies.
